number of segments). The data-base consists of a large parallel literary corpus (Le petit prince and translations thereof) which is complemented by further sources of information such as descriptive grammars. The data are analyzed from a synchronic perspective. However, diachronic issues are addressed unsystematically, too. It is shown that the distribution of phenomena which characterize paradigms of spatial interrogatives are subject to areal-linguistic factors. This is the first typological study of spatial interrogatives. It provides new insights for students of the grammar of space, morphological paradigms, and language typology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxMorphology. 0aLanguage and languagesxVariation. 0aLinguistics. 4aConstructional Complexity. 4aLinguistik. 4aMorphological Mismatches. 4aSpatial Interrogatives. 4aTypologie. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aLevkovych, Nataliya, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aNintemann, Julia, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aRobbers, Maja, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aUrdze, Aina, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2017z9783110547887oZDB-23-DSP0 cEPUBz97831105383350 cprintz978311053275340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311053951640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110539516423Coveruhttps://www.degruyte